"Myung S.-T., Amine K., Sun Y.-K.","Surface modification of cathode materials from nano-to microscale for rechargeable lithium-ion batteries",2010,"Journal of Materials Chemistry","20","34",,"7074","7095",,,10.1039/c0jm00508h,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77955812169&partnerID=40&md5=e1c63e6f085e86dfe4816d1995ce5133","Department of Chemical Engineering, Iwate University, 4-3-5 Ueda, Morioka Iwate 020-8551, Japan; Electrochemical Technology Program, Chemical Sciences and Engineering Division, Argonne National Laboratory, 9700 South Cass Avenue, Argonne, IL 60439, United States; Department of WCU Energy Engineering, Hanyang University, Seoul 133-791, South Korea; Department of Chemical Engineering, Hanyang University, Seoul 133-791, South Korea","Myung, S.-T., Department of Chemical Engineering, Iwate University, 4-3-5 Ueda, Morioka Iwate 020-8551, Japan; Amine, K., Electrochemical Technology Program, Chemical Sciences and Engineering Division, Argonne National Laboratory, 9700 South Cass Avenue, Argonne, IL 60439, United States; Sun, Y.-K., Department of WCU Energy Engineering, Hanyang University, Seoul 133-791, South Korea, Department of Chemical Engineering, Hanyang University, Seoul 133-791, South Korea","The present concern with global warming urgently requires a large increase in the energy share provided by green, renewable energy sources, as well as massive commercialization of sustainable vehicles. The widespread availability of reliable energy storage systems and highly efficient lithium batteries can, in principle, meet this need. For example, many individuals already own at least one lithium-ion battery portable device, such as a cellular phone, MP3 player, digital camera, or laptop computer. Hybrid electric vehicles and full electric vehicles will sooner or later be marketed with lithium-ion batteries. However, to acquire an established role in the commercial sector, lithium-ion batteries must be improved with regard to energy density, cost, and particularly, safety. Further development of electrode materials, especially the cathode active materials, is important to satisfy the above requirements. The easiest route to cathode improvement is to modify the cathode surface. This article describes recent advances in cathode active materials with surface modification from the nano-to microscale. © 2010 The Royal Society of Chemistry.",,"Cathode active material; Cathode improvements; Cathode materials; Cathode surface; Cellular Phone; Commercial sector; Electrode material; Energy density; Further development; Hybrid electric vehicle; Lithium-ion battery; Micro-scales; MP-3 players; Portable device; Reliable energy; Renewable energy source; Surface modification; Automobiles; Cameras; Cathodes; Electric vehicles; Global warming; Ions; Laptop computers; Lithium; Lithium alloys; Lithium compounds; Renewable energy resources; Secondary batteries; Surfaces",,,,,,"Tarascon, J.-M., Armand, M., (2001) Nature, 414, p. 359; Armand, M., Tarascon, J.-M., (2008) Nature, 451 (652), p. 2008; Bruce, P.G., Scrosati, B., Tarascon, J.-M., (2008) Angew. Chem., Int. Ed., 47, p. 2930; Dahn, J.R., Sleigh, A.K., Shi, H., Way, B.M., Weydanz, W.J., Reimers, J.N., Zhong, Q., Von Sacken, U., (1994) Lithium Batteries: New Materials, Developments and Perspectives, pp. 1-47. , ed. G. Pistoia, Elsevier, Amsterdam; Nagaura, T., (1991) JEC Battery Newslett, 2, pp. 17-25. , (March-April); Nagaura, T., (1991) Prog. Batteries Solar Cells, 10, p. 209; Thackeray, M.M., (1995) J. Electrochem. Soc., 142, p. 2558; Manthiram, A., Kim, J., (1998) Chem. Mater., 10, p. 2895; Komaba, S., Kumagai, N., Sasaki, T., Miki, Y., (2001) Electrochemistry, 69, p. 784; Myung, S.-T., Komaba, S., Kumagai, N., (2001) J. Electrochem. Soc., 148, p. 482; Banov, B., Todorov, Y., Trifonova, A., Momchilov, A., Manev, V., (1997) J. Power Sources, 68, p. 578; Amine, K., Tukamoto, H., Yasuda, H., Fujita, Y., (1996) J. Electrochem. Soc., 143, p. 1607; Amine, K., Tukamoto